Hey <@807494421088043018> , regarding adding cachyOs repos to pacman:

Cachyos runs a script during install to check you machine hardware and adds repo with packages compiled for different cpu generations.
It will add cachyos-v3, cachyos-v4 or cachyos-zenver4 to pacman.conf depending on CPU version.

See here for more details:
https://wiki.cachyos.org/features/optimized_repos/

You might be able to implement the script in the orchestrator. 
https://mirror.cachyos.org/cachyos-repo.tar.xz is the script.
